  "text": "System identification has been a field of much interest to the robotics and controls community for decades. More recently, the techniques of inverse kinematics and feedback linearization have been used to actuate robots to track desired motion trajectories. Such approaches, like many other modelbased controllers, rely on high-gain Proportional-Derivative controllers to compensate for inaccurate dynamics models, leading to non-compliant and potentially dangerous behavior [CITATION_1] . Additionally, model-learning is of interest to the reinforcement learning community because of its data-efficiency compared to model-free methods [CITATION_2] and potential for transfer during continual learning [CITATION_3] , [CITATION_4] . Hence, learning dynamics models using data, or simply fine-tuning models crafted from prior knowledge, has been approached in several ways.",
